A LED-based temperature sensor.

Files:
.pde - Arduino code
.png - Diagram PNG
.fz - Fritzing diagram

Hardware required:
* (1) Arduino board (I used an Arduino Uno)
* (1) Boradboard (I used an Adafruit Proto Shield)
  - http://www.adafruit.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=17_21&products_id=51
* (2) Potentiometer 
* (2) LED (I used one blue & one red)
* (1) TMP-102 board /TI SOT563 (I used a TMP-102 from SparkFun)
   - http://www.sparkfun.com/products/9418 
* (17) Connectors/wires
